:"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ezr","bookOrder":14,"chapter":2,"verse":58,"text":"All the temple servants","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ezr:2:59","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ezr","bookOrder":14,"chapter":2,"verse":59,"text":"The following are those who came from Tel-melah, Tel-harsha, Cherub, Addan, and Immer but were unable to prove that their ancestral families and their lineage were Israelite:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ezr:2:60","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ezr","bookOrder":14,"chapter":2,"verse":60,"text":"Delaiah’s descendants,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ezr:2:61","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ezr","bookOrder":14,"chapter":2,"verse":61,"text":"and from the descendants of the priests: the descendants of Hobaiah, the descendants of Hakkoz, the descendants of Barzillai —who had taken a wife from the daughters of Barzillai the Gileadite and who bore their name.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ezr:2:62","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ezr","bookOrder":14,"chapter":2,"verse":62,"text":"These searched for their entries in the genealogical records, but they could not be found, so they were disqualified from the priesthood.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ezr:2:63","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ezr","bookOrder":14,"chapter":2,"verse":63,"text":"The governor ordered them not to eat the most holy things until there was a priest who could consult the Urim and Thummim.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ezr:2:64","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ezr","bookOrder":14,"chapter":2,"verse":64,"text":"The whole combined assembly numbered 42,360","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ezr:2:65","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAb